[49m[39m  166, 166[0m:[39m[49m def get_icd10_suggestions(clinical_text: str) -> list:
[0m[49m[39m  167, 167[0m:[39m[49m     """
[0m[49m[39m  168, 168[0m:[39m[49m     Call Amazon Comprehend Medical's InferICD10CM API.
[0m[49m[39m  169, 169[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  170, 170[0m:[39m[49m     The API returns a list of medical condition entities found in the text.
[0m[49m[39m  171, 171[0m:[39m[49m     Each entity includes:
[0m[49m[39m  172, 172[0m:[39m[49m       - Text: the span that triggered detection ("Type 2 diabetes")
[0m[49m[39m  173, 173[0m:[39m[49m       - Category: always MEDICAL_CONDITION for this API
[0m[49m[39m  174, 174[0m:[39m[49m       - Traits: list of attributes (NEGATION, DIAGNOSIS, SIGN, SYMPTOM, etc.)
[0m[49m[39m  175, 175[0m:[39m[49m       - ICD10CMConcepts: ranked list of code suggestions with confidence scores
[0m[49m[39m  176, 176[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  177, 177[0m:[39m[49m     The API handles negation internally. "Patient denies chest pain" will still
[0m[49m[39m  178, 178[0m:[39m[49m     return an entity for "chest pain" but it will have the NEGATION trait, which
[0m[49m[39m  179, 179[0m:[39m[49m     we filter on in Step 3.
